@sokra thanks for taking the time to have a look at this issue.

> you shouldn't nested webpack bundles

does that mean that webpack 5 no longer supports importing libraries made by webpack? this same example works in webpack 4.

It's not related to `devtool`, but to the fact that webpack dev server does not work with library target anymore.
Specifically dev server client is being exported instead of the given entry.
Since its export is an empty object that's where `Cannot read property 'call' of undefined ` comes from.

I created a very simple reproduction of the issue:
[webpack-entry-point-bug-repro.zip](https://github.com/webpack/webpack/files/5105052/webpack-entry-point-bug-repro.zip)

Steps to run:
```
yarn install
yarn dev
```

Then go and check the `./dist/main.js` or `http://localhost:8080/main.js`.
Last lines of compiled code will be like this:

```
/******/ 	// module exports must be returned from runtime so entry inlining is disabled
/******/ 	// startup
/******/ 	// Load entry module and return exports
/******/ 	__webpack_require__("./main-entry.js");
/******/ 	return __webpack_require__("./node_modules/webpack-dev-server/client/index.js?http://localhost:8080");
/******/ })()
;
```
Which means that dev client is exported. 

Is there any way to make webpack concatenate entries in the specified (in entry array) order?
And export the last of them as a library?

@dmitrysteblyuk Because we have the same issue but not related to webpack-dev-server

